<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1789,2010]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1437,152,1570]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,323,1945,1971]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. In wing pattern, the species is indistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName box="[1006,1151,1945,1970]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spatulata">
<emphasis box="[1006,1151,1945,1970]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. spatulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, known from the same locality. The main differences in male genitalia between 
<taxonomicName box="[814,923,1984,2009]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gnoma">
<emphasis box="[814,923,1984,2009]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. gnoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[979,1117,1984,2009]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spatulata">
<emphasis box="[979,1117,1984,2009]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. spatulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the following: (
<number box="[1350,1362,1984,2010]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1.0">1</number>
) apex of cucullus in 
<taxonomicName box="[316,424,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gnoma">
<emphasis box="[316,424,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. gnoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with one small upcurved tooth (
<figureCitation box="[799,885,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 40" captionStartId="15.[151,270,1617,1641]" captionTargetBox="[173,1416,202,1592]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,90,1593]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 40. Perittia gnoma sp. n., male genitalia. 37, valvae, juxta and phallus; 38, uncus, tegumen, gnathos and vinculum. Holotype, gen. prep. MRAC / KMMA 0 0 473, specimen ID: RMCA ENT 0 0 0 0 0 5176. Scale bar 0.1 mm. 39, valva; 40, apical part of phallus and juxta lobes (a, juxta lobe). Paratype, gen. prep. MRAC / KMMA 0 0 474, specimen ID: RMCA ENT 0 0 0 0 0 5177." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189259/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number box="[853,885,152,178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="39.0">39</number>
</figureCitation>
), in 
<taxonomicName box="[936,1073,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spatulata">
<emphasis box="[936,1073,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. spatulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with several minute teeth (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 47" captionStartId="18.[151,270,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[177,1382,196,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,154,1872]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 47. Perittia spatulata sp. n., male genitalia. 44, general view (juxta and phallus removed); 45, juxta and phallus, lateral view. Paratype, gen. prep. MRAC / KMMA 0 0 464, specimen ID: RMCA ENT 0 0 0 0 0 5160. Scale bar 0.1 mm. 46, lateral part of genitalia; 47, apical part of phallus and juxta lobes (a, spatula shaped process of phallus; b, juxta lobe). Holotype, gen. prep. MRAC / KMMA 0 0 463, specimen ID: RMCA ENT 0 0 0 0 0 5159." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189261/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,185,190,216]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="46.0">46</number>
</figureCitation>
); (
<number box="[216,232,190,216]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
) inner surface of cucullus in 
<taxonomicName box="[580,719,191,216]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spatulata">
<emphasis box="[580,719,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. spatulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without tapering process, in 
<taxonomicName box="[1065,1175,191,216]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gnoma">
<emphasis box="[1065,1175,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. gnoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with tapering process (
<figureCitation box="[160,309,229,255]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 40" captionStartId="15.[151,270,1617,1641]" captionTargetBox="[173,1416,202,1592]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,90,1593]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 40. Perittia gnoma sp. n., male genitalia. 37, valvae, juxta and phallus; 38, uncus, tegumen, gnathos and vinculum. Holotype, gen. prep. MRAC / KMMA 0 0 473, specimen ID: RMCA ENT 0 0 0 0 0 5176. Scale bar 0.1 mm. 39, valva; 40, apical part of phallus and juxta lobes (a, juxta lobe). Paratype, gen. prep. MRAC / KMMA 0 0 474, specimen ID: RMCA ENT 0 0 0 0 0 5177." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189259/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Figs. 
<number box="[229,309,229,255]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="37.39">37, 39</number>
</figureCitation>
); (
<number box="[342,357,229,255]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
) sacculus meeting cucullus at sharp angle (about 
<number box="[961,1038,229,255]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="65.0" valueMax="80.0" valueMin="50.0">50–80</number>
º) in 
<taxonomicName box="[1095,1207,229,254]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gnoma">
<emphasis box="[1095,1207,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. gnoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
versus blunt angle (about 
<number box="[233,336,268,294]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="127.5" valueMax="145.0" valueMin="110.0">110–145</number>
º) in 
<taxonomicName box="[390,532,268,293]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spatulata">
<emphasis box="[390,532,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">E. spatulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; (
<number box="[556,572,268,294]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="4.0">4</number>
) ventral shield of juxta about 
<number box="[924,934,268,294]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[945,961,268,294]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
length of phallus in 
<taxonomicName box="[1203,1312,268,293]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gnoma">
<emphasis box="[1203,1312,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. gnoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, about 
<number box="[1398,1411,268,294]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="in" value="4.0">4 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName box="[182,325,306,331]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spatulata">
<emphasis box="[182,325,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. spatulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; (
<number box="[352,368,306,332]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="5.0">5</number>
) apex of phallus pointed in 
<taxonomicName box="[709,822,306,331]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gnoma">
<emphasis box="[709,822,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. gnoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[838,987,306,332]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 40" captionStartId="15.[151,270,1617,1641]" captionTargetBox="[173,1416,202,1592]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,90,1593]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 40. Perittia gnoma sp. n., male genitalia. 37, valvae, juxta and phallus; 38, uncus, tegumen, gnathos and vinculum. Holotype, gen. prep. MRAC / KMMA 0 0 473, specimen ID: RMCA ENT 0 0 0 0 0 5176. Scale bar 0.1 mm. 39, valva; 40, apical part of phallus and juxta lobes (a, juxta lobe). Paratype, gen. prep. MRAC / KMMA 0 0 474, specimen ID: RMCA ENT 0 0 0 0 0 5177." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189259/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Figs. 
<number box="[907,987,306,332]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="37.4">37, 40</number>
</figureCitation>
), in 
<taxonomicName box="[1041,1183,306,331]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Perittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spatulata">
<emphasis box="[1041,1183,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. spatulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with broad, strongly sclerotized process (
<figureCitation box="[389,532,345,371]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 47" captionStartId="18.[151,270,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[177,1382,196,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,154,1872]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 47. Perittia spatulata sp. n., male genitalia. 44, general view (juxta and phallus removed); 45, juxta and phallus, lateral view. Paratype, gen. prep. MRAC / KMMA 0 0 464, specimen ID: RMCA ENT 0 0 0 0 0 5160. Scale bar 0.1 mm. 46, lateral part of genitalia; 47, apical part of phallus and juxta lobes (a, spatula shaped process of phallus; b, juxta lobe). Holotype, gen. prep. MRAC / KMMA 0 0 463, specimen ID: RMCA ENT 0 0 0 0 0 5159." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189261/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
